The date of St Ninian’s death is almost, if not indeed altogether, as uncertain as any other event in his life, with the single exception mentioned above September 16, 432, has been usually given, sometimes as on the authority of Bede‚ and sometimes as on that of Ailred ς but the date is to be found in neither writer. The author of the Scottish Legends of the Saints gives September 16, 332, which is probablya mistake for September 16, 432 ; and if so, we have in this tradition of the Fourteenth Century, a confirmation of the generally accepted date Other dates given are 437 and 512.
